    "SchemaContract": {
      "additionalProperties": false,
      "description": "Schema contract configuration for controlling schema evolution.\n\nControls three dimensions of schema evolution at the destination:\n\n1. **tables**: Can new tables be created?\n   - evolve: Allow new tables (recommended for Bronze, needed for first run)\n   - freeze: Block new tables (raises PipelineStepFailed)\n   - discard_row: Drop rows for unknown tables\n   - discard_value: Not applicable for tables dimension\n\n2. **columns**: Can new columns be added to existing tables?\n   - evolve: Allow new columns (flexible, good for development)\n   - freeze: Block new columns (strict production governance)\n   - discard_row: Drop entire row if new column detected\n   - discard_value: Set new column values to NULL, keep row\n\n3. **data_type**: Can column data types change?\n   - evolve: Allow type changes (may cause issues)\n   - freeze: Block type changes (recommended for production)\n   - discard_row: Drop row if type mismatch\n   - discard_value: Set mismatched values to NULL\n\nRecommended Defaults:\n    - Development: tables=evolve, columns=evolve, data_type=evolve\n    - Production: tables=evolve, columns=freeze, data_type=freeze\n\nWhy tables=evolve in production?\n    - First run: Tables don't exist yet, dlt must create them\n    - Child tables: dlt auto-creates nested tables (e.g., orders__items)\n    - New tables: When you add a new table to config\n\nReference: https://dlthub.com/docs/general-usage/schema-contracts\n\nExample YAML:\n    schema_contract:\n      tables: evolve      # Allow table creation\n      columns: freeze     # Block new columns\n      data_type: freeze   # Block type changes",
      "properties": {
        "columns": {
          "$ref": "#/$defs/SchemaEvolutionMode",
          "default": "freeze",
          "description": "Control new column addition (evolve, freeze, discard_row, discard_value)"
        },
        "data_type": {
          "$ref": "#/$defs/SchemaEvolutionMode",
          "default": "freeze",
          "description": "Control column type changes (evolve, freeze, discard_row, discard_value)"
        },
        "tables": {
          "$ref": "#/$defs/SchemaEvolutionMode",
          "default": "evolve",
          "description": "Control new table creation (evolve, freeze, discard_row, discard_value)"
        }
      },
      "title": "SchemaContract",
      "type": "object"
    },
    "SchemaEvolutionMode": {
      "description": "Schema evolution modes for dlt schema_contract.\n\nReference: https://dlthub.com/docs/general-usage/schema-contracts",
      "enum": [
        "evolve",
        "freeze",
        "discard_row",
        "discard_value"
      ],
      "title": "SchemaEvolutionMode",
      "type": "string"
    },
